  "prompt": "What are the main reasons why students from Boston University don't graduate on time?",
  "response": "There can be several reasons why students from Boston University, or any university, may not graduate on time. Some of the main reasons typically include:\n\n1. **Academic Challenges**: Students may struggle with coursework, leading to failing grades or the need for retaking classes, which can extend their time to graduation.\n\n2. **Major Changes**: Many students change their major during their college years. This can result in the need to take additional or different courses, delaying graduation.\n\n3. **Financial Issues**: Some students face financial difficulties that may affect their ability to enroll in classes or pay tuition on time, leading to delays in their educational progress.\n\n4. **Personal Issues**: Personal circumstances, such as health problems, family responsibilities, or mental health challenges, can interfere with a student\u2019s ability to maintain a full course load.\n\n5. **Course Availability**: Limited availability of required courses can force students to postpone graduation. This can happen if popular classes are full or not offered every semester.\n\n6. **Extracurricular Commitments**: Students heavily involved in extracurricular activities, part-time jobs, or internships may find it challenging to balance responsibilities with their academic workload.\n\n7. **Advising and Support**: Lack of effective academic advising or support services can lead to students not being aware of necessary requirements or failing to meet them.\n\n8. **Transition Issues**: Adjusting to college life can be difficult for some students, and they may require time to acclimate to the demands of higher education.\n\nAddressing these issues often involves a combination of institutional support, proactive advising, and personal strategies to help students stay on track for timely graduation.",
